OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784731730
OL,3,CDeadly pox outbreak threatens nature
OL,4,Creserve's red squirrel population
OL,6,FAn urgent warning has been issued
OL,7,Fafter a deadly outbreak of squirrelpox
OL,8,Fwas confirmed in one of England's last
OL,9,Fremaining red squirrel strongholds.
OL,11,FThe Lancashire Wildlife Trust (LWT)
OL,12,Fsays the coming weeks will be
OL,13,F"critical" for the survival of the
OL,14,Fendangered animals in Formby and is
OL,15,Fcalling on the public to take
OL,16,Fimmediate action to stop the spread.
OL,18,FSquirrelpox is carried by invasive,
OL,19,Fnon-native grey squirrels, who can
OL,20,Fspread the virus unnoticed without
OL,21,Fsuffering any symptoms.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/8
