CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F366A1784731730
OL,3,CDeadly pox outbreak threatens nature
OL,4,Creserve's red squirrel population
OL,6,FRed squirrels are Britain's only
OL,7,Fnative squirrel species. Historically
OL,8,Fnumbering in the millions and found
OL,9,Facross the country, the population has
OL,10,Fdrastically declined to an estimated
OL,11,F287,000, with around three-quarters of
OL,12,Fthose now living in Scotland.
OL,14,FIn England, the remaining populations
OL,15,Fare confined to isolated pockets,
OL,16,Fmaking localised outbreaks
OL,17,Fcatastrophic.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
